Description: Handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Circular stamp; rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.28a, 22. The type is known from Paphos and the Benaki collection, Alexandria Museum.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0968)
